n't bother you. It wasn't an issue for us because we were on the 9th floor.--The doorman has maps to help guide you around the city and the top tourist destinations.--The red line is a short walk away from the hotel on W Chicago. My wife and I walked from the subway station to the hotel with our luggage without any problem. The hotel is in a GREAT location. There's a bus stop right out front, as well. The No. 22 Clark runs you downtown and all throughout the River North neigbhorhood the hotel is in.--Plenty of food options nearby. Portillos is right down the street on N Clark. They have great Italian beef sandwiches, Chicago hot dogs, and my wife got some great pasta. It's not a fancy place at all, just a walk up and eat cafeteria. A great option for a quick bite to eat so you can avoid going to McDonalds across the street. Also, Yolks is fantastic. We ate breakfast there before we left. It's right around the corner on N Wells. A must for brunch or meal before you leave town. A Whole Foods is two blocks away for the hotel on W Huron. Great for picking up snacks for the room or for the day.Bottom line: The Hotel Felix was a safe, clean hotel in a great location. It provided my wife and I a great place to drop our bags and see all that Chicago has to offer.	
