May 15 2009 	Euro design with relaxing tones and modern decor.	The Hotel Felix had recently opened, they were still hanging their marque when I arrived. I entered a small lobby with two conversation lounge areas and bar near a fireplace for intimate socializing. The decor was a soothing eco-friendly setting for a professional or trendy meet place. The front desk staff was very friendly and were especially accommodating to all of our requests, as were the bellman (who even ran to the store for me). I only experienced single rooms, which were quite small but efficiently designed for storage &amp; comfort. The feel of the room was modern with earth tones for a relaxing atmosphere. The queen size bed had drawers built into the platform, eliminating the need for a dresser. There was soft cotton bedding, fluffy pillows and a duvet comforter on a very comfy mattress. The bathroom had a roomy stone tile stall shower with no tub, with a modern basin, non harsh lighting, thick cotton towels and hotel toiletries. To keep the room uncluttered, the flat paneled TV was wall mounted, a reduced size club chair was placed in a corner. The only horizontal place to put things were the compact desk area with wifi, a small modern table next to the club chair and two night tables on either side of the bed. The closet was compact but adequate for the single room. I missed out on the fitness room and spa (tight schedule), but I used the business center, which had free internet service and a printer/fax. There were also several meeting rooms, which looked comfortable when I peeked in.As far as I know, my group very satisfied with the hotel, with no memorable complaints, except one who had trouble navigating around the platform bed.Dont miss the restaurant ZED451 just one block away. Its a wonderful eclectic mix of American, Asian and Mediterranean choices for a one price, serving up a variety of inventive flavor infused, dry rubbed and aged meats plated in a Churrasco serving style. Very chic multi level decor with some seating extending from a fire pit. Bring an appetite, since the food doesnt stop until you realize that there is no more room to experience another bite.	
May 13 2009 	Very chic very new very nice hotel!	I booked the Hotel Felix through a conference I was attending in Chicago. This was my first time to Chicago, so I had no idea on ideal locations, but the Felix was perfect! It was within walking distance to almost everything I wanted to see, and if something was too far to walk, the doormen were eager to assist me with either a cab or instructions to the &quot;L&quot; Trains. As others have said, the rooms were small, but for a single traveler, they were just perfect. I was there for eight days and never felt cramped. The bed was possibly the most comfortable hotel bed I have ever slept on. The rooms came with free Wi-Fi which was nice being there on business, and included HD TV's and iPod docking stations which was great. The front desk staff was extremely friendly and helpful, and all of the doormen were excellent. Most of the time I was there, I dealt with Julian, and every time I went somewhere he took the time to ask where I was going and if I needed directions, and every time I returned he asked how each specific experience was. Each doorman remembered my name after asking it only once. The housekeeping staff was always around when I would leave the room, and would always ask if I wanted service or if I wanted them to wait. I was extremely impressed with the entire staff. My overall impression of the Hotel Felix was definitely a positive one, and if I ever return to Chicago, I will be staying there again!	
