Apr 16 2009 	good economincal hotel	Revisiting Chicago where I used to live, I wanted an economical 3 day stay. I had a queen room on the 12th floor - you should know it's NYC size small! For myself , it was fine, if 2 people, may be difficult in that there is NO place to put your bag so even though it's cozy and cute small, it's not practical at all. Was told their bathrooms only had showers - no bathtub/shower combo options in the entire hotel exist. The bed is very comfy and I think they put forth a nice design to the whole place. They offer free continental breakfast each day which is nice. Service was fine. Whole Foods is 2 bl. away and Huron/Clark is an easy cab ride to Old Town and points to Loop - for business it'd work great.My complaint has to do with how loud everything was - thin walls, their sinks in the bathrooms are a bit weird - very shallow, they could use some basic options in the room like a do not disturb sign because the cleaning crew starts knocking on doors at 6:30am! Their spa opens this week and their restaurant was still in process of getting ready to open in June I was told. I typically stay at Sofitel Watertower or Sutton Place Hotel in Gold Coast for location which have larger rooms. I travel quite a bit and enjoy 4star hotels - I would likely not stay here again but for the value and if you were solo travelling for just 1-2 nights on business, it's a worthwhile stay. They've tried to make it a 4 star hotel w. the spa, business ctr, free wi-fi, etc. but the substance isn't really there. For $85 night it was worth it but I would be disappointed if I had to have paid more for it.	
