Apr 6 2009 	Nicely remodeled hotel in good location	The Hotel Felix is a newly remodeled property that just opened for guests in March 2009. The location is excellent, just a couple of blocks from Michigan Avenue (Magnificent Mile) and near lots of popular sites. The hotel has a modern slightly European decor. The rooms are small and a bit cramped, but the space is utilized well. The small rooms are not really a problem for most people because you're probably not coming to this part of Chicago to hang out in your room. The staff were attentive and helpful. Our room had no bulbs in the lamp and a non-functional phone when we checked in. These were fixed immediately. The beds are very comfortable. The hotel is trying to be green, so valet parking is free if you have a hybrid car. Otherwise it's a very pricey $42/day. There was a little confusion at check-out. I'd already pre-paid on Hotwire, but was asked to pay again. The problem was solved however and not really an issue. Overall this is a nice place, with a great location in the heart of Chicago.	
